Website - Bhuvan GeoNetwork (Data Discovery) 
Website URL - https://bhuvan.nrsc.gov.in/geonetwork
Website Content Details -
Bhuvan Geonetwork is a free and open-source web-based geospatial data portal developed by the National Remote Sensing Centre (NRSC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). It provides a single point of access to a wide range of geospatial data and information from India and around the world.

Bhuvan Geonetwork is built on the GeoNetwork open-source platform, which is a powerful and flexible framework for managing and sharing geospatial data. The portal features a user-friendly interface that makes it easy to find and use geospatial data. It also provides a variety of tools and services for working with geospatial data, including:

Data search and discovery: Bhuvan Geonetwork provides a powerful search engine that allows users to find geospatial data by location, topic, and other criteria.
Data visualization: Bhuvan Geonetwork provides a variety of tools for visualizing geospatial data, including maps, charts, and tables.
Data analysis: Bhuvan Geonetwork provides a variety of tools for analyzing geospatial data, including spatial analysis, statistical analysis, and machine learning.
Bhuvan Geonetwork is a valuable resource for anyone who needs to access or use geospatial data. It is especially useful for government agencies, businesses, and researchers who need to make informed decisions about the use of land, resources, and infrastructure.

Here are some of the key features of Bhuvan Geonetwork:

It is free and open-source, so anyone can use it.
It provides access to a wide range of geospatial data from India and around the world.
It has a user-friendly interface that makes it easy to find and use geospatial data.
It provides a variety of tools and services for working with geospatial data.
Bhuvan Geonetwork is a powerful and versatile tool that can be used for a variety of purposes. It is a valuable resource for anyone who needs to access or use geospatial data.
